[
    {
        "content": "<p>Can I please get some reviews for <a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/all/20240930-static-mutex-v4-1-c59555413127@google.com/\">https://lore.kernel.org/all/20240930-static-mutex-v4-1-c59555413127@google.com/</a> ?</p>",
        "id": 476085131,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728551756
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"519727\">Alice Ryhl</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/288089-General/topic/Global.20locks/near/476085131\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Can I please get some reviews for <a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/all/20240930-static-mutex-v4-1-c59555413127@google.com/\">https://lore.kernel.org/all/20240930-static-mutex-v4-1-c59555413127@google.com/</a> ?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>FYI, <code>b4</code> is complaining about DKIM for your email:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Text only\"><pre><span></span><code>Checking attestation on all messages, may take a moment...\n---\n  ✓ [PATCH v4] rust: add global lock support\n  ---\n  ✓ Signed: openpgp/aliceryhl@google.com\n  ✗ BADSIG: DKIM/google.com\n---\nTotal patches: 1\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 476130261,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1728565710
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's probably the LKML forwarding <span aria-label=\"woman shrugging\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f937-200d-2640\" role=\"img\" title=\"woman shrugging\">:woman_shrugging:</span></p>",
        "id": 476131904,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728566181
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I sign all patches with my pgp key. That'll have to be good enough.</p>",
        "id": 476133594,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728566662
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>so I'm reading the <a href=\"http://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/CAH5fLgh9kHm4XbcH2X4y6nwZ9VLYuUeu3hNmQBcdZ+Vx1H1L9w@mail.gmail.com\">discussion</a> for v2, but I fail to understand why we need macro even for cases where locked_by and guard are not needed.</p>",
        "id": 476160806,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1728573868
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Once we get rid of the initialization step, the macro will always be needed for mutexes due to them being self-referential</p>",
        "id": 476160994,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728573924
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We don't need that for spinlocks though</p>",
        "id": 476161036,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728573936
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but what the macro does is only wrapping locks in a $wrapper, I think we can implement a <code>GlobalLock&lt;T, Backend&gt;</code> type instead of defining the $wrapper type, no?</p>",
        "id": 476161582,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1728574086
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If we get rid of it we have to reintroduce it when we want to eliminate the init step</p>",
        "id": 476161794,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728574158
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That seems silly</p>",
        "id": 476161808,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728574164
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Why have such churn?</p>",
        "id": 476161847,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728574174
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, the macro does nothing special today. But it will need to.</p>",
        "id": 476162035,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728574224
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>My hope is that we can do pin-init for static variable as well. So we don't need that macro eventually.</p>",
        "id": 476162192,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1728574278
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'll believe it when I see it</p>",
        "id": 476162311,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728574315
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm not willing to be blocked on that one</p>",
        "id": 476162547,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728574377
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>a lot of stuff needs to be done in order to achieve that, it is a \"hard\" issue :)</p>",
        "id": 476162728,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1728574435
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think the current macro approach is fine</p>",
        "id": 476162805,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1728574445
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Sure, but \"not able to do pin-init for static variable\" is what seems silly to me ;-)</p>",
        "id": 476162825,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1728574450
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>we can improve pin-init and then later change it</p>",
        "id": 476162861,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1728574460
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah, but it is rather complicated</p>",
        "id": 476162896,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1728574470
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>we need constant closures</p>",
        "id": 476162908,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1728574475
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>here is a more complete list:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>constant traits</li>\n<li>constant closures</li>\n<li>a way to actually use an <code>impl PinInit&lt;T&gt;</code> to initialize a static</li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 476163363,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1728574614
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"519727\">Alice Ryhl</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/288089-General/topic/Global.20locks/near/476161794\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>If we get rid of it we have to reintroduce it when we want to eliminate the init step</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>(wrong question, deleted)</p>",
        "id": 476163846,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1728574762
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"519727\">Alice Ryhl</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/288089-General/topic/Global.20locks/near/476160994\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Once we get rid of the initialization step, the macro will always be needed for mutexes due to them being self-referential</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>By \"once we get rid of the initialization step\", you mean we have the const values for lock initialization, right? But, it won't work for mutexes (because of pinning), so we still need the actually init() step. By \"the macro will always be needed\", you mean you need the macro to construct the <code>init()</code> function for mutexes?</p>",
        "id": 476165606,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1728575284
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Trying to understand what the macro will do in the future...</p>",
        "id": 476166169,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1728575464
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's possible to avoid the init step even for mutexes, but it's not possible to define a const fn for it because it needs to know it's own address.</p>",
        "id": 476166878,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728575698
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess we could have an unsafe const_new that takes a raw pointer to the address it will have, and then returns a value to store at that address.</p>",
        "id": 476166952,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728575722
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So the <code>global_lock</code> macro will help avoid the init step for mutexes? What will it do exactly?</p>",
        "id": 476167756,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1728575965
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>in the future.</p>",
        "id": 476167804,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1728575983
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It'll just expand to </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">static</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MUTEX</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mutex</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">const_new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">addr_of</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">MUTEX</span><span class=\"p\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 476168002,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728576032
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I.e. if we can have a <code>const_new</code>, then we probably don't need a macro (other than the locked_by cases).</p>",
        "id": 476168465,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1728576139
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>if we cannot have a <code>const_new</code>, we cannot skip the init() step, so <code>global_lock</code> will work as today, and it does nothing special. So we don't need it for simple cases (no locked_by needed).</p>",
        "id": 476168897,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1728576247
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The macro makes const_new safe.</p>",
        "id": 476169111,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1728576300
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh, I see.</p>",
        "id": 476169187,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1728576319
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Now the discussion on v2 makes sense to me, sorry for being slow ;-)</p>",
        "id": 476171557,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1728576863
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm super happy with how the new implementation turned out. Check out this example:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">sync</span><span class=\"p\">::{</span><span class=\"n\">GlobalGuard</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">GlobalLockedBy</span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">sync</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">global_lock</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\">// SAFETY: Initialized in module initializer before first use.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">uninit</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">static</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MY_MUTEX</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Mutex</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"sd\">/// All instances of this struct are protected by `MY_MUTEX`.</span>\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">MyStruct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">my_counter</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">GlobalLockedBy</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MY_MUTEX</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MyStruct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// Increment the counter in this instance.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">///</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// The caller must hold the `MY_MUTEX` mutex.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">increment</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">guard</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">GlobalGuard</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">MY_MUTEX</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">my_counter</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">my_counter</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_mut</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">guard</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">my_counter</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">my_counter</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Module</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MyModule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">_module</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">ThisModule</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// SAFETY: called exactly once</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MY_MUTEX</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">init</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">MyModule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{})</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 478506111,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1729692610
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It looks great Alice!</p>",
        "id": 478511230,
        "sender_full_name": "Marcelo Borges",
        "timestamp": 1729694031
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It is interesting that you can have a type and a static with the same name. It is what makes the <code>GlobalLockedBy&lt;u32, MY_MUTEX&gt;</code> syntax work.</p>",
        "id": 478511393,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1729694069
    }
]